2. What is a pod?
Ans. Kubernetes pod is a collection of one or more containers and they share same resources. Pod is created using a .yaml file which contains all the specifications of a pod along with the configuration information that determines how a container should run. Itâ€™s the smallest execution unit in Kubernetes. Pods can be terminated at any point and then restarted on another node within our Kubernetes cluster.
K8s pod to run an instance of an application. We can scale out an application by adding more pod replicas

